column5: has anybody stayed there and hows the fishing? walleyes northern,ect

Have stayed at Mylie's several times, and will be there in 60 days for the Walleye opener. Great accomodations and terrific owners. Great walleye and northern fishing in that area. What time of year are you looking at? Marv
Justin runs a great place, and the fishing is phenominal in the area.

Obabikon I believe is the owner of a resort in Obabikon Bay. Hats off to him for positive comments on a competitors resort. Also hats off to him for the fishing information he provides thru the fishing seasonI've stayed at Mylies a total of about 20 weeks over the years and highly recommend it.
I stayed there last fall. We were up fishing for Muskie and some walleye. We didn't have much luck, but others in camp did Ok. Nice place and recently remodeled cabins, good beds etc. I would go back
FH I'll be there the 21st thru the 28th. Send me a PM. I'll give you some info. Marv
I've been going there for 10 years .Great people and great walleye and northern fishing not too far from camp.
Hey Marv, How did you guys do on the opener? We will be at the Obabikon resort on 6/18. Hopefully you left some fish for us.
